  <subsection xml:id="subsec-converting-temperature-in-degrees-celsius-to-kelvin">
    <title>Converting temperature in degrees Celsius to Kelvin.</title>
    <explanation>
      <p>
        To convert temperature from degree celsius to Kelvin, add 273 to the temperature in degree Celsius.
      </p>
    </explanation>
    <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Convert <m>47^\circ C</m> to Kelvin.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <md>
          <mrow> K =\amp ^\circ C + 273 </mrow>
          <mrow> =\amp47^\circ C +273 </mrow>
          <mrow> =\amp320 K </mrow>
          <mrow> 47^\circ C = \amp 320 K  </mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          The temperature of a room was <m>25^\circ C.</m>  What was the temperature of the room to Kelvin?
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <md>
            <mrow>K =\amp ^ \circ +273  </mrow>
            <mrow> =\amp 25^\circ C + 273</mrow>
            <mrow> =\amp 298K </mrow>
          </md>
        </p>
        <p>
          The temperature of the room was <m>{\color{magenta}298\text{K}}</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </example>
    <example>
  <statement>
    <p>
     When Daven fell sick ,her temperature rose to <m>39.5 ^\circ C</m>. What was her temperaturein Kelvin?
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      <md>
        <mrow>K = \amp ^\circ C  </mrow>
        <mrow> = \amp (273 + 39.5)</mrow>
        <mrow> = \amp 311.5K </mrow>
      </md>
    </p>
  </solution>
</example>
